# Shared widgets & reuse (screens and UI)

Whenever you **create or substantially edit** a screen, route page, or reusable UI block:

## 1. Search first
- **Search the codebase** for an existing widget or pattern that matches the need (same layout, button style, field, list row, dialog, loading state, etc.).
- Check in order:
  - `lib/shared/widgets/` — **preferred** home for app-wide UI building blocks (e.g. `app_primary_button.dart`, `app_text_field.dart`, `app_otp_field.dart`, `app_skeleton_loader.dart`, **`app_google_map.dart`**, `map_widgets.dart`).
  - `lib/core/widgets/` — cross-cutting, low-level helpers tied to core (e.g. `svg_picture_asset.dart`).
  - Feature folders `lib/features/<feature>/presentation/widgets/` — only when the UI is **feature-specific** and not reusable elsewhere.

## 2. Prefer existing shared components
- If a suitable widget **already exists** under `lib/shared/widgets/` (or an appropriate feature widget), **use or extend it** instead of duplicating markup and styling in the screen file.
- Do **not** introduce a second “primary button” or “text field” pattern in a feature if `AppPrimaryButton` / shared text field already exists—align with those APIs and theming.

## 3. When to add something new to `lib/shared/widgets/`
- Add a **new** file under `lib/shared/widgets/` only when the component is (or clearly will be) used in **more than one feature or screen**, or is part of the **design system** (buttons, inputs, chips, sheets).
- Use clear names with a consistent prefix (e.g. `app_`) matching existing files in that folder.

## 4. Shared functions / helpers
- If logic will likely be used in **multiple places** (formatting, validation snippets, dialog helpers, mappers used across features), place it in **`lib/shared/utils/`** (or a small dedicated file under `lib/core/` if it is infrastructure-only, e.g. network-related).
- Avoid copying the same private helper into multiple feature files; extract once and import.

## 5. Conflict with Figma one-off screens
- A screen can still be composed **from** shared pieces even when matching a Figma frame—assemble shared widgets with local layout/spacing rather than reinventing primitives each time.

If a task explicitly requires a one-off prototype, note that in the PR/description; still prefer shared pieces where they fit without fighting the design.

## 6. Duplication rule (explicit)
- If the **same visual + interaction** (or the same Figma component) already exists or will appear on **more than one screen**, **extract it once** under `lib/shared/widgets/` (or extend an existing shared widget) **in the same change** unless the user explicitly asks for a one-off.
- Do **not** copy-paste map chrome, headers, chips, sliders, or buttons into a new screen when an equivalent already exists in the repo—search, then reuse or generalize with parameters.

## 7. Google Map (mandatory)
- **Never** embed the raw `GoogleMap` widget from `google_maps_flutter` in feature screens or feature-local widgets.
- **Always** use **`AppGoogleMap`** from `lib/shared/widgets/app_google_map.dart` (or import the barrel **`lib/shared/widgets/map_widgets.dart`** for `AppGoogleMap` + map chrome + **`AppMapService`** in one place).
- **Projection / defaults:** use **`AppMapService`** (`lib/core/services/app_map_service.dart`) for helpers like `screenOffsetFor`; do not duplicate `getScreenCoordinate` error handling in features.
- If a new map capability is needed app-wide (e.g. extra `GoogleMap` parameters), **extend `AppGoogleMap` in `lib/shared/widgets/`** in the same change — do not add a second map wrapper in a feature folder.
